tldr: The user wanted to improve the aesthetics of their sleep questionnaire
  app. I implemented a new calming, sleep-themed color palette, redesigned key
  UI components like the progress bar, cards, and form fields, and enhanced
  section layouts to create a more professional and engaging user experience.
overview: The user wanted to elevate the aesthetic appeal of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they felt was too generic. I initiated a
  comprehensive design overhaul, starting with a detailed analysis of the
  existing UI. The approach involved replacing the standard color palette with a
  calming, sleep-themed scheme of indigos, purples, and teals. Key components
  like the QuestionnaireForm, IntroSection, Progress bar, Card elements, and
  various form fields (CheckboxField, RadioGroupField, Slider) were meticulously
  restyled. This included adding subtle background blurs, star patterns, feature
  cards, and improved hover/active states for interactive elements. The goal was
  to transition the app from a basic, template-driven look to a more
  sophisticated, trustworthy, and emotionally resonant interface suitable for a
  sleep health application. After implementing these changes and confirming
  successful compilation, I began a visual review in the browser to ensure the
  desired aesthetic was achieved.
